    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSimilar to #31384 (which was fixed by #31387), but with expanding extmarks (i.e. `right_gravity = false` and `end_right_gravity = true`).\nSeems to be a #31387 regression.\n\ncc @luukvbaal \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create the  following 'init.lua':\n    ```lua\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, { 'abc abcd' })\n    vim.api.nvim_win_set_cursor(0, { 1, 3 })\n\n    _G.ns_id = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('extmark')\n    local extmark_opts = { end_col = 3, hl_group = 'Search', right_gravity = false, end_right_gravity = true }\n    _G.mark_id = vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, _G.ns_id, 0, 0, extmark_opts)\n\n    vim.o.completeopt = 'menuone,noinsert'\n    ```\n2. `nvim --clean -u path/to/init.lua`\n3. Press `i` and `<C-n>`. It should show popup with `abcd` as candidate while extmark is still intact.\n4. Type `e`. Extmark is not extended to the right (although it should). I presume because it is restored as it was *before* text is inserted. Executing `:=vim.api.nvim_buf_get_extmark_by_id(0, ns_id, mark_id, { details = true })` confirms that both `right_gravity` and `end_right_gravity` are correct.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExtmark correctly tracks text change, i.e. expands to the right.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1272+g3d3a99e69c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have this functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.12.1-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 0.1.0-main+3c637a27\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
