            "body": "Another way to reproduce similar issue (extmarks are restored as they were before text edit) is to add an extmark with `right_gravity = true` at the column where completion leader changes:\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, { 'abc abcd' })\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_cursor(0, { 1, 3 })\n\n_G.ns_id = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('extmark')\nlocal extmark_opts = { end_col = 6, hl_group = 'Search', right_gravity = true, end_right_gravity = true }\n_G.mark_id = vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, _G.ns_id, 0, 3, extmark_opts)\n\nvim.o.completeopt = 'menuone,noinsert'\n```\n\nAll other steps are the same. Expected behavior is for the highlighted region to shift to the right (which is the case before #31387).",
