            "body": "There is another indicator that current behavior is disruptive (more than it was before #31387): `vim.snippet` is now more broken in certain cases than it used to be.\n\n1. Create the following 'init.lua':\n    ```lua\n    vim.o.completeopt = 'menuone,noselect'\n\n    vim.keymap.set('i', '<M-m>', function() vim.snippet.expand('abc $1 abd $2') end)\n\n    _G.get_snippet_extmarks = function()\n      local ns_id = vim.api.nvim_get_namespaces()['vim/snippet']\n      return vim.api.nvim_buf_get_extmarks(0, ns_id, 0, -1, { details = true })\n    end\n    ```\n2. `nvim --clean -u path/to/init.lua`\n3. Enter Insert mode and press `<M-m>`.\n4. Type `ab`, `<C-n>`. The popup should be visible.\n5. Type `e`. Popup disappears and so is snippet highlighting. Executing `:get_snippet_extmarks()` confirms that snippet session stopped (no extmarks present). Before #31387 it continued to exist, however pressing `<Tab>` and adding characters highlighted the whole range from start of first tabstop and to the end of second.",
